race.description: Tilly's Earthmoving Spare Parts Mdn Hcp
race.comment: CHEEKY'S TIME (9) started a short-priced favourite over 1000m at Dalby but found a couple better. She'd been beaten less than 2L at the Sunshine Coast prior and that's the benchmark for her chances. Peaks today with Cartwright reunited and she is well-placed to break through. ZOUSAIN GIRL (11) progressed nicely here last time beaten 1.5L over this distance. Maps well and will be fitter again. Has winning claims. LADY BARBAROSSA (10) has the ability but gives away big starts. She made up plenty of ground to just miss here two back and has trialled since the flop at the Gold Coast last time. Will have to do it the hard way again but can make the finish with average luck. TROOPER SAM (7) also presents third-up and has a handy 3kg claim. He went close here before the spell and should be suited by the step up in trip. BLUEY'S CHOICE (5) is also capable of better and has a 2kg claim.
